Hi All,

I'm an independent AI researcher specializing in genetic programming. I
think I have found some alternative approaches for the topics covered in
this group, and I'm hoping to get some feedback from anyone who has the
time to read my preprints describing these ideas.

The first one describes a way to do neuroevolution using genetic
programming. The obvious advantage is that the evolved solution is a
human-readable computer program rather than a black box:

http://arxiv.org/abs/1901.11090

The second one started out for me as a better way to seed initial
populations of programs for a genetic programming system, rather than
random or hand-coded seeding, but I see now that it is relevant to Ken
Stanley's work on novelty search:

http://arxiv.org/abs/1901.11115

Thank you!
David Landaeta
Natural Computation LLC
